history.content:
When I took it last fall, the average was 21.3 and median was 21.5. SD was 6.87. Keep in mind that the maximum score was 40-41. Hope that helps!


Edit from another user:

Hilfinger's final also included a section of his graphs project on the final. This means that if you didn't do the project(3), that section was practically impossible. Even people who did it had problems with it. His projects come back to bite you when you least expect it...
When I took it last fall, the average was 21.3 and median was 21.5. SD was 6.87. Keep in mind that the maximum score was 40-41. Hope that helps!

children.subject: thank you so much, this is really encouraging! i needed this comment :)

That is not to say the exam is remotely easy though lol, and you should still try to get as many points on the projects and EC as possible while you can. If I were you I would try to depend as little as possible on the exams as they can be rough to score in, in an absolute (not relative) sense.

Also keep in mind that the average/median can be artificially low as a LOT of people didn't need to score much on the final last fall to get the grade they desired, so quite a few people ended up leaving really early after having attempted what they felt would be enough to score what they needed to get said grade.
